## Detailed Defect Reports

### DEF-003: Predator false positives

**Description:** Robot detected predator when object moved slowly, causing unnecessary wing openings.

**Steps to Reproduce:**
1. Place hand 30cm from front sensor
2. Move hand toward robot slowly (5cm/s)
3. Observe wings opening prematurely

**Root Cause:** Distance drop threshold was too low (10cm/cycle)

**Fix Applied:** Increased threshold to 15cm/cycle

**Verification:** Tested on 14 April — false positives eliminated

---

### DEF-005: Obstacle turn not sharp enough

**Description:** Robot turned too gradually when obstacle detected, sometimes still hitting object.

**Steps to Reproduce:**
1. Place obstacle 18cm in front
2. Observe turn angle

**Root Cause:** Turn duration too short

**Fix Applied:** Increased turn duration in gait code

**Verification:** Tested on 14 April — clean turns, no collision

